# .secretsignore — allow-list for scripts/check-no-secrets.sh
#
# One POSIX extended-regex per line. A flagged line that ALSO matches any rule
# here is treated as a legitimate placeholder / public reference, not a leak.
# Prefer adding a narrow rule here over weakening a detection pattern.

# The public maintainer/org handle. It appears legitimately in homepage URLs,
# author fields, and audit docs (which even quote "/home/agricidaniel/" while
# asserting no such paths leak). It is NOT a private local username, so a
# developer's own /Users/<username>/ home path is still caught.
/(Users|home)/agricidaniel/
